headlines.description: — Jalen Johnson had 20 points and nine assists, De'Andre Hunter added 18 points and the Atlanta Hawks handed the Charlotte Hornets their fifth straight loss 107-104 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Johnson scores 20 points, Hawks hang on to beat Hornets 107-104 for 3rd straight win

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey scored 28 points and the Philadelphia 76ers won their fourth game of the season by beating the Detroit Pistons 111-96 on Saturday night.

— Giannis Antetokounmpo had 42 points, 12 rebounds and 11 assists in his return to Milwaukee’s lineup and the Bucks won their sixth in a row by beating the struggling Washington Wizards 124-114 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo has 42 points, 12 rebounds and 11 assists, Bucks win 6th straight 124-114 over Wizards

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 27 points, Kevin Durant added 21 and the Phoenix Suns beat the Golden State Warriors 113-105 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker scores 27, Suns win 113-105 as Warriors lose their 4th straight game

headlines.description: — Kyrie Irving scored 30 points and Quentin Grimes had 24 points to power the short-handed Dallas Mavericks over the Utah Jazz 106-94 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irving pours in 30 and Grimes scores 24 as Dallas wins again without Doncic, 106-94 over Utah
